      <hedline>
        <hl1>Bush vs. Gore, Round 1: Now the People Debate; Shades of Yogi</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>George Solovay letter comments on remarks about role of military made by Gov George W Bush during debate with Vice Pres Al Gore on October 3</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I wonder if Yogi Berra helped George W. Bush prepare for the debate. Answering a question about the military, Mr. Bush said, ''I believe the role of the military is to fight and win war and therefore prevent war from happening in the first place'' (transcript, Oct. 4).</p>
        <p>GEORGE SOLOVAY  Florham Park, N.J., Oct. 4, 2000</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
